  <!-- TOPIC SECTIONS (12) -->
  <main class="container" id="topics-container">

    <!-- Topic 1 -->
    <article id="topic-1" class="info-box reveal">
      <div>
        <div class="info-title">Phishing Awareness</div>
        <div class="info-text">
          Phishing is when attackers masquerade as trustworthy parties (banks, services, colleagues)
          to trick you into revealing credentials, OTPs, or installing malware.
        </div>
        <div class="subpoints">
          • Check sender address and domain. <br>
          • Hover links before clicking. <br>
          • Be suspicious of urgent requests. <br>
          • Verify via official channels if unsure.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-media">
        <!-- fixed/stable CDN image -->
        <img alt="Phishing email example" src="https://picsum.photos/id/1025/900/600">
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Topic 2 -->
    <article id="topic-2" class="info-box reveal">
      <div>
        <div class="info-title">Strong Passwords</div>
        <div class="info-text">
          Strong passwords are long, unique, and random. Reusing passwords across sites is dangerous.
        </div>
        <div class="subpoints">
          • Use at least 12 characters. <br>
          • Mix upper/lowercase, numbers & symbols. <br>
          • Use a reputable password manager to create & store them.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-media">
        <img alt="Strong password" src="https://picsum.photos/id/1050/900/600">
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Topic 3 -->
    <article id="topic-3" class="info-box reveal">
      <div>
        <div class="info-title">Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)</div>
        <div class="info-text">
          2FA requires a second verification (SMS, authenticator app, hardware key) after entering your password.
        </div>
        <div class="subpoints">
          • Prefer authenticator apps or hardware keys over SMS. <br>
          • Enable 2FA for email, banking and social accounts. <br>
          • Keep backup codes secure.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-media">
        <img alt="Two factor authentication" src="https://picsum.photos/id/1005/900/600">
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Topic 4 -->
    <article id="topic-4" class="info-box reveal">
      <div>
        <div class="info-title">Safe Browsing</div>
        <div class="info-text">
          Safe browsing practices reduce the chance of infection or data theft while online.
        </div>
        <div class="subpoints">
          • Look for HTTPS and the lock icon. <br>
          • Avoid unknown downloads and cracked software. <br>
          • Keep browser & plugins updated.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-media">
        <img alt="Safe browsing" src="https://picsum.photos/id/1060/900/600">
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Topic 5 -->
    <article id="topic-5" class="info-box reveal">
      <div>
        <div class="info-title">Social Engineering</div>
        <div class="info-text">
          Social engineering exploits human trust and emotions — attackers may impersonate colleagues or officials.
        </div>
        <div class="subpoints">
          • Don't act under pressure; verify identity. <br>
          • Be cautious with phone calls asking for sensitive info. <br>
          • Train teams to spot manipulation tactics.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-media">
        <img alt="Social engineering" src="https://picsum.photos/id/1027/900/600">
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Topic 6 -->
    <article id="topic-6" class="info-box reveal">
      <div>
        <div class="info-title">Malware Protection</div>
        <div class="info-text">
          Malware includes viruses, spyware, and ransomware. It can steal or lock your files and spy on activity.
        </div>
        <div class="subpoints">
          • Install reputable antivirus and keep it updated. <br>
          • Avoid unknown USBs and attachments. <br>
          • Regularly back up important data offline.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-media">
        <img alt="Malware protection" src="https://picsum.photos/id/1011/900/600">
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Topic 7 -->
    <article id="topic-7" class="info-box reveal">
      <div>
        <div class="info-title">Data Privacy</div>
        <div class="info-text">
          Data privacy is about controlling who can access your personal information and how it's used.
        </div>
        <div class="subpoints">
          • Limit app permissions. <br>
          • Review privacy settings on social platforms. <br>
          • Think before sharing personal details.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-media">
        <img alt="Data privacy" src="https://picsum.photos/id/1043/900/600">
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Topic 8 -->
    <article id="topic-8" class="info-box reveal">
      <div>
        <div class="info-title">Digital Footprint</div>
        <div class="info-text">
          Your digital footprint is the record of what you post and do online — it can affect future opportunities.
        </div>
        <div class="subpoints">
          • Clean up old accounts. <br>
          • Use privacy settings and think before posting. <br>
          • Remember search engines retain cached info.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-media">
        <img alt="Digital footprint" src="https://picsum.photos/id/1035/900/600">
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Topic 9 -->
    <article id="topic-9" class="info-box reveal">
      <div>
        <div class="info-title">Cyberbullying</div>
        <div class="info-text">
          Cyberbullying harms mental health. It should be reported to platform moderators and, when needed, authorities.
        </div>
        <div class="subpoints">
          • Block and report abusive users. <br>
          • Save evidence (screenshots). <br>
          • Talk to trusted adults or professionals.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-media">
        <img alt="Cyberbullying" src="https://picsum.photos/id/1021/900/600">
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Topic 10 -->
    <article id="topic-10" class="info-box reveal">
      <div>
        <div class="info-title">Network Security</div>
        <div class="info-text">
          Network security protects devices and data on local and wide-area networks using controls like firewalls and segmentation.
        </div>
        <div class="subpoints">
          • Change default router passwords. <br>
          • Use WPA3 or WPA2 for Wi-Fi encryption. <br>
          • Segment guest network from main devices.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-media">
        <img alt="Network security" src="https://picsum.photos/id/1003/900/600">
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Topic 11 -->
    <article id="topic-11" class="info-box reveal">
      <div>
        <div class="info-title">VPN &amp; Encryption</div>
        <div class="info-text">
          VPN encrypts your traffic between you and a server. Encryption protects data at rest and in transit.
        </div>
        <div class="subpoints">
          • Use a trusted VPN on public Wi-Fi. <br>
          • Prefer services with strong encryption (AES-256). <br>
          • Encrypt backups and sensitive files.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-media">
        <img alt="VPN encryption" src="https://picsum.photos/id/1015/900/600">
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Topic 12 -->
    <article id="topic-12" class="info-box reveal">
      <div>
        <div class="info-title">Cloud Security</div>
        <div class="info-text">
          Cloud services provide convenience but require strong access controls, backups, and monitoring.
        </div>
        <div class="subpoints">
          • Enable 2FA for cloud accounts. <br>
          • Use strong, unique passwords. <br>
          • Regularly back up and monitor access logs.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="info-media">
        <img alt="Cloud security" src="https://picsum.photos/id/1033/900/600">
      </div>
    </article>

